<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-70-0110 </DOCNO><TEXT>The availability of part-time positions may be changing because of pressurescreated by the reimbursement policies of insurance companies, HMOs, andthe government. While some positions may be created by those wantingto pay only for services directly received, other part-time positionsmay be absorbed by larger groups desiring additional income. Physiciansdesiring part-time employment should be aware of the prevailing economicforces. The salary scale and privileges vary widely. The increasing numberof part-time professional employees has made it clear that certain standardsof reimbursement, insurance coverage, and vacation must be developed.The legal rights of part-time employees are being defined and are presented.</TEXT></DOC>